Windows 10 Version 10.0.19043 Build 19043

I'm encountering a very strange issue.
When I load my front-end app (static HTML and JS files) for the first time, it works perfectly, the files are served, and the app displays immediately in the browser.

If I reload the page, the same files get requested to the Deno server (index.html, Javascript files) but some of them, always the same ones, remain pending. It's always `polyfill.js` and `main.js`. The application remains loading.....

......but not forever. After 17 minutes (I made the test earlier today), the two JS files get unstuck, served, and the app gets displayed in the browser.

![2022-01-13_114338](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3706912/149338099-392b380d-9a7a-49c0-94d4-ab6652133580.png)

I believe it has to do with the file size, because the two that always get stuck are also the two heaviest of the lot.

I have made a repository with the minimal code (2 TS files + some static front-end files to be served) to reproduce the issue : https://github.com/jeremythille/deno_serving_issue

I have also made a 5 minute screen recording to demonstrate the issue on my machine: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1KXzT7sE9ah9A_1YVxWFkblqEWAO5Jk_p/view?usp=sharing

Below is the code from index.ts (it's in the repo):

```
import { router } from "./router.ts"

const port = 8090;

const server: Deno.Listener = await Deno.listen({ port });
console.log(`Deno server listening on http://localhost:${port}/`);

for await (const conn: Deno.Conn of server) {
  const httpConn = Deno.serveHttp(conn);
  for await (const { request:req, respondWith:res } of httpConn) {
    const response: Promise<Response> = router(req);
    res(response); // The only place where we respond to the browser
  }
}
```


This is just standard (async iterator), minimal code I've found in the Deno documentation. It works, but only once, not on page reload.

And I'm reading the files with this line :

`const file = await Deno.readFile(distDir + "/" + fileName);`

Not sure if I'm doing something wrong, or if it is a bug...?

